items.text: Small cafe, good service. Expect to queue. Must tries: Honey Paprika Chicken Wings, Sunny side stacked sandwich (Loved the butter croissant)
What's not to like about the place? Good food, good coffee, friendly service! Even the music is great!
Overall if you love lunch and love taking photos of food, Lola is the place to be! The food is great and really instragrammable. When we reached at 10:05am, the waiting time is already 1 hour!
Yummy honey paprika chicken wings!
Long queue!!!!
Flat white is good but the mushroom cheese sandwich is underwhelming.
Their reservation system surprised me! Key-in your mobile number & you'll know what I mean.
The Cheesy Mushroom Toast gets a thumbs up from me!👍😊 This cafe is very affordable but it's way too crowded and you have to make a reservation days before popping by😕
Only finger food from 3pm to 6pm
Loved the crab spaghetti and the Belgian ales.
Tried Bangers & Mash. The mashed potatoes are pretty good; I enjoyed them without needing the sauce.
You gotta try their popcorn chicken starter, it's fried with their home-made batter. Good stuff
Try the lemo meringue tart! Die also need tryb
Good service, good food.
Amazing paprika crispy wings and butter croissant. They really know how to play with the taste.
Get the wings and the Bangers and mash. Friendly staff as well
Had a Flat White without sugar. Too sour for my liking. Seasalt chocolate tart is pretty good.
Waiting time can be relatively long. Bangers and Mash is really good. If you're a tea lover, Iced Marigold Round Tea is the best drink hands down.
Honey paprika crispy wings is super delicious! A Must-try starter dish!
Atlantic Egg is really good for. Brunch, coffee could have been bette though.
Came here midweek in the afternoon thinking i can have peaceful quaint time sitting in cafe. NOT. Prepare to queue and inside is packed cos cafe is really small.
Coffee is good. V popular cafe though. So either come early or be prepared to queue.
Chicken wings, big breakfast and eggs benedict were orgasmic.  First place I've ever tried their chai tea and no other place has beat them since.
Desserts aren't that worth the long queue. Lola's chocolate cake was too sweet with cream that tasted grainy
We had fish and chips, granchio spaghetti, brownie, chocolate mousse today. All are tasty. This young team has got quality. Great service to boot. Ever ready to offer advice. Enjoy!
Eggs Benedict were delicious
Great food and nice staffs, but hope they can make more menu items..
The truffles fries smells nice, looks good but taste seriously need to improve as it is very starchy! The cafe "Sunday Market" still makes the best truffles fries!!!
Avocado Egg Benedict was good.
Good coffee. Vanilla caramel black tea. Lemon meringue tart. Scrambled egg croissant. Avocado egg benedicts.
It's mainly good for brunch. Lunch options are limited. Haven't had chance to try dinner yet.
Rude staff. Nice food.
Returned to try the starters. Good bangers & mash, but $10 is pricey for just 2 sausages. Paprika wings are definitely more worth it!
Hmm nothing special , banger&mash , lemon tart was good, chicken wings so so
Good thing they have chai latte. Fried chicken is average, sausage is quite fab and ice cream is really good.
Rating: normal taste. Good drink choices. Warm veggies, probably veg from the day before. Unpleasant avocados and lots of egg shells
Good coffee
Honey crispy wings is quite addictive!
Nothing else but the chicken wings... just the chicken wings.
Seems to always have a queue. However, the wait is totally worth it! Love the Bangers & Mash the most! the mashed potatoes is highly recommended!
Aside from coffee, they also serve one of the best hot chocolates I've ever tasted in Singapore. Perhaps I'm just overhyping, but you can try it for yourself.
Breakfast was not great. Hollaindaise sauce needs major improvement. I had a tummy ache after having the Eggs Benny...
Awesome service !
Finally our turn after waiting for an hour ! Hungry hungry but service is great (:
Yummy Breaky! Didn't expect them to survive so long since the day one we visit them when they started biz! Now they expanded to the next door! Looks like getting more popular!
Starters are good. Tarts are not bad too. Service is great
On an overall, the food is surprisingly good for a cafe. Place is pretty nice and prices are affordable. Signature wings are a must try!
GREAT place and Great service 😍
love it! and my parents went back for coffee and enjoyed it too. more pics and details at http://www.eatprayflying.com/new-cafe-review-lolas-cafe-simon-road-kovan/ :)
disappointed with the wings on my latest visit. taste so different from before.
Expanded with two shop spaces ie. more seating area, the cafè is still packed at most times of the day. Flat white/lattès ordered are robust and truffle fries come in an ample sharing portion.
这个鸡翅膀还不错吃哦！
Make sure you make reservation. . It will be quite crowded. They hv nice chic wings
The bacon in the butter croissant made the overall taste too salty for my liking but the croissant itself was good. The eggs in Eggs Ben was done nicely. Not bad Lola. :)
Braised pork goulash is a must try. Comfort food for the soul. 👍
Can get crowded during the weekends, but they have an online queueing system at the entrance that's quite useful. You get an automated call once it's your turn.
The buffalo chicken is super tasty and nice!! I even take away after having it in the cafe :D
Excellent Eggs Atlantic (eggs Benedict w/ smoked salmon) and very good iced black coffee (espresso drinks seem good here). Very popular; people were queueing with the Chope tablet.
Smart queuing, nice ambience and pleasant food topped with friendly service. What's not to like 👍
It's always crowded.
Honey crispy wings and beef goulash is very good. Fish and chips is over fried.
Quality coffee, thick chocolate. 👍
Prepare to wait for a really long time if you don't come early. place is small as are the portions. can't go wrong for people staying nearby to call a brunch place their own. Food is a miss for me.
They say Lola has one of the best chicken wings in SG. Okay i agree. Must try must try!!
Coffee is delicious.
Poor seating arrangement!Table is flimsy and too small. Hard to eat in peace without worrying the utensils might fall!
Give me those chicken wings and nacho fries and I am yours! 😌
Tuna sandwich's pretty good!
2 poached eggs seated well with  slices of salmon pieces on brioche bread . A hot chocolate to complement a gd brunch
Love the food!
Food was good, had the pork goulash, duck confit and the honey wings. Service staff was very friendly but service could have been a little more attentive.

no soft drinks here. Hubby ordered a chai latte and it came with cinnamon powder on top which is not written in the menu and they refused to change. Very disappointing and never gonna come here again.
Butter croissant is a must try. BUT, stay away from the Eggs Benny. Low grade ham and runny sauce. Couldn't finish the dish.

Only came here once, queue is ridiculous and the time to wait for food not worth it. The chicken wings are awesome but that's all I can remember. I prefer less crowded places without waiting too long.
Their honey paprika wings, so damn delicious !
very good nacho cheese fries
Long queue on weekends! Unless you don't mind sharing tables, you might end up waiting long. Good coffee and brunch. Dessert so so. Good service considering how busy it was.
Queue is forever long. Good coffee but was out of soy and skinny milk on a Sunday morning? Good Chai Latte. Chicken wings are good. Eggs Benedict has too much hollandaise sauce.
Cash or nets only. Food's good. Happy with my order of avocado egg ben.
Small place, be ready to wait quite a bit for your seat!
Affordable desserts. Nutella tart is a little more pricey but it's worth a try! Has a slight tinge of saltiness to reduce the 'gelat-ness'
